<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101168388819346></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101168388819346><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5933&mid=101168388819346>RE: 5th Shawl</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5933&mid=101168388819346#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=22775><span id=Guru>SuBoneTL</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>85 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 22nd 3:19 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you hunt the Wurms at night you can save yourself a lot of time.&nbsp;&nbsp;You're looking for glowing bile, because the wrms that drop it actually do glow.  It'll just look like they have a GLS; you'll see light on the ground around them.  Don't mistake their light for the Crystal Shards on the ground, though.  I might be mistaken, but I think Crystalline Threads can only be combined in a Coldain Kit.  Also, Fiber/Bile combos aren't failable.  Good luck, and be safe.<br>&nbsp;<br>Hyden Endabrush<br>Expert Scout of the Fay</td></tr>
